Unfortunately my SR had its first mechanical failure in the 4 years I’ve beat on it. After my second lap of the day I noticed my oil pressure gauge was reading 0 pressure, and it was making a metallic ticking sound. I quickly shut it off and towed it off track. We removed the rocker cover and discovered the noise was the timing chain slapping the upper guide, and not a bottom end knock! It appears that I saved it in time…

It’s going to be quite the experience tearing into the old SR

I’ve been trying to keep busy while the SR20 is being built. Engine parts have all arrived and the refresh has finally begun. This semester is a relatively light one for me so I’ve had some free time to tinker around on the S13. I restored my valve cover to a factory finish, and painted the set of Z32 calipers I picked up!my seat and other bride components were also refreshed, and I began prepping the engine bay for paint!

PS: if anyone knows how to restore a Greddy oil cap, I’m all ears lol

Normally I’d wait until the car looks presentable but I’m too excited not to share some JZZ30 content! @tweed_autogarage did it again for me. GT-C’s have been a bucket list wheel for a long time and I’m very happy to finally own a set in Face 2. It’s been so fun to tinker around with this thing the last couple of weeks! It’s been an awesome daily driver. That said if anyone has some cheap coilovers for this thing I’d love to pick some up 😅

Life update: I accepted the offer at UT Arlington and I’ll be starting in January! This meant I needed a cheap commuter since the SC is sitting on ~ 320k miles 😅

I found this CPV35 in Arlington for a decent price and spec’d out how I’d want one!  It needed (needs) some work, but I gotta say… I’ve been having so much fun un-ruining this thing😅
Reunited and it feels so goood 🎶
What a great way to end an awesome year! I’m hoping to have this thing running and driving before February!
